South African ventriloquist Conrad Koch hits the Johannesburg stage this month with his latest one-man show, "Puppet Guy". The show dives into the politics of South Africa in a light-hearted and joyful manner, he says. In an interview with HuffPost editor at large Ferial Haffajee, Koch explained that he had do a great deal of emotional interrogation in order to create a show that does not alienate any group of people. The ventriloquist behind the controversial puppet Chester Missing shares his journey to finding the lighter side of politics in South Africa. Watch as Conrad Koch shares the journey of making "Puppet Guy".   The show will run at Montecasino from April 25 - May 27. Keen to find out who will be featured in the show? Conrad Koch gives HuffPost a teaser of the wild and wacky characters to expect. Watch: 